name: Photographs: A Walk in the Woods

metadata.name: Appearances are Deceptive
metadata.description:
A Walk in the Woods by Hulki Okan Tabak

An imaginary journey through sculpted woods where strangers vanish into deceptive forest canopy strewn with ancient monuments, elder trees and splashes of water. 

An outdoor journey towards the inner self, towards a greater unity with -- what?

Inspired by the beauty and the mystery of nature which both within and outside.

1/1 photographs created with landscape photography, AI prompts and final manual editing.

"somewhere i have never travelled, gladly beyond  
any experience, your eyes have their silence:  
in your most frail gesture are things which enclose me,  
or which i cannot touch because they are too near"  
---from somewhere i have never travelled, gladly beyond by e. e. cummings
